author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "CLI command consumes a JSON array of {op:create|update|close} mutations on stdin and applies them atomically via the public SDK commitItemMutations only (no private-core imports); partial failure compensates per the SDK policy and reports per-mutation outcomes; --dry-run previews the batch; unknown ops/keys fail fast with contract-derived hints; idempotent resume via a stable --transaction-id; MCP parity tool + contracts/completions/docs/vitest wiring per the new-command checklist; command naming decided under the pm-pbyu noun-verb composition input before implementation"
parent: pm-usfg
risk: medium
confidence: 75
resolution: SDK-backed atomic batch mutations are available through pm item mutate and pm_mutate with strict validation and recovery controls.
expected_result: CLI and MCP accept typed atomic create/update/close batches through the public SDK without private-core coupling or partial writes.
actual_result: "CLI and MCP share strict structured parsing, public SDK commitItemMutations dispatch, dry-run, idempotent resume, compensation, finite lock validation, contracts, docs, and 100% coverage."
