comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-20T07:55:26.190Z",codex-20260720,"Implementation start 2026-07-20: coherent broad bundle pm-xm7c + pm-kipd + pm-nilh + pm-cfed + pm-g9xk + pm-ds3b. All-status duplicate checks confirmed pm-y9hq is the closed SDK prerequisite rather than duplicate work; GH-435/437/438/443 and GH-595 map to the existing canonical items. GitHub intake: open Dependabot PRs #618-#621; #619 and #620 currently have one failed coverage shard each; open Dependabot alerts=0, secret-scanning alerts=0; Scorecard code-scanning alerts #17-#23 remain represented by pm-gnzh/pm-qwoy and are outside this implementation bundle."
  "2026-07-20T09:12:28.393Z",codex-20260720,"GitHub intake refresh 2026-07-20: Dependabot and secret-scanning open alerts remain zero; Scorecard code-scanning alerts #17-#23 remain represented by the existing security lineage. Dependency PRs #618 and #621 are green; #619 and #620 each have one failed coverage shard. New GitHub issue #623 had no all-status duplicate and is now documented as open pm-mfkv92, related to the closed merge/history lineage but outside this active structured-I/O bundle."
  "2026-07-20T09:59:52.215Z",codex-20260720,"Evidence: delivered SDK-backed atomic mutation batches across CLI (pm item mutate) and MCP (pm_mutate), strict typed parsing, dry-run, replay/resume, compensation controls, contract snapshots, and CLI/MCP parity tests. Linked structured suite passed after making author resolution environment-explicit; full repository coverage passed 6012/6012 at 100/100/100/100. Packed temp proof committed two mutations atomically with status=committed, recovered=false, mutation_count=2."
  "2026-07-20T10:26:24.049Z",codex-20260720,"Greptile finding disposition: MCP atomic mutations now reject non-finite or non-numeric lock TTL/wait values with a usage error before SDK dispatch; number, numeric-string, and invalid-type branches are covered. Full coverage is 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-20T10:41:22.047Z",codex-20260720,"Second Greptile P1 disposition: replaced transport-specific coercion with shared public SDK parseAtomicMutationControls used by both CLI and MCP; finite lock values and close/delete compensation are validated before dry-run or commit. Focused suites pass and full coverage is 6014/6014 at exact 100/100/100/100."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-20T07:55:27.225Z",codex-20260720,"Design boundary: one agent-native structured IO platform—contract-derived JSON parsing, SDK-only atomic execution, compact projections, CLI/MCP parity, and deterministic errors—rather than independent flag handlers."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-20T07:55:28.316Z",codex-20260720,All-status lineage shows structured input and compact output share contract/schema/projection infrastructure; shipping them together reduces duplicated validation and gives review bots one coherent end-to-end surface.
  "2026-07-20T09:59:52.787Z",codex-20260720,Linked tests must establish PM_AUTHOR explicitly when asserting author fallback because pm test intentionally propagates the invoking agent identity into its sandbox.
